I always wear athleisure and fitness clothes so I wanted to create my own line that I felt empowered in. Which I why I created @manifest_body ! 

A full line of athletic and athleisure clothes for powerful and empowered women! 

I love feeling and looking good while being active or running errands. Every piece is  SO supportive and and comfy. 

Manifestbody is about Manifesting the best version of YOU. I want to empower women to love themselves and honor their bodies wherever they are on their journey. You deserve to feel ALL THE TIME. 

Thank you to all the women who have been purchasing from @manifest_body since Friday! I can’t wait to see you in your pieces ✨✨✨

node.text:
Whew. Apparently I can’t talk about “body positivity” because I have natural curves ? 🥴

Let’s unpack this. From ages 13-17 I suffered from a eating disorder. A very real one. Had to go therapy and see a nutritionist weekly. In middle school where was constantly called “fat” or asked if I have failed several grades because my body was so developed. My hair was referred to as “nappy” so I would straighten it every day. 

In highscool I barely ate and tried to survive off 800 calories a day. I also then was a virgin and shammed by everyone in my grade for how my body naturally looked. So much to the point I stopped even defending the rumors and let people believe it. This is when I went to private online schooling and graduated at 16 because my depression was so bad. 

At 17 i went to beauty school and was surrounded by grown women living in their truth. It inspired to wear my hair natural and embrace my curves, dips, and hips. It took time even after that for me to love myself. Before having a “curvy” body was trendy this was my body and still is my body. 

It’s beyond frustrating when people especially women come on page to tell me I can’t speak on body positivity because I’m curvy or have half a million followers. 

I’m here to let you know I worked years to love myself. So I’m going LOVE myself loudly. Every inch of me. I constantly get dms from other women saying how I have inspired or helped them love something about themselves they used to hate. So I will continue to show all these juiciness and love it. 😜

I want you to love yourself loudly too. I want you feel empowered in your swimsuit too. I don’t care what shape or size you are. You are beautiful and never let anyone tell you that you aren’t! ❤️🙏🏽✨

Being positive about your body doesn’t look one way. Anyone of any shape or size can be positive about their body. In fact that should be the goal. For us all to love ourselves ✨ In fact I did a interview with @bluecentric in 2020 on this topic, maybe it’s time revisit the conversation.

You don’t serve you self by playing small. Wake up and attack those goals! You are capable of achieving anything you put your mind and intentions to!

People think if they say something it will just “manifest” into their lives. This only one part to manifestations. We have to our forth action to receive what we want. The power of actually manifesting is doing the work and trusting the process ✨🙏🏽❤️
